NAME		tzadjust
SYNTAX		tzadjust [adjustment]
DESCRIPTION	tzadjust is used to set up a timezone adjustment on a per
		user basis. Without arguments, the command will show your
		current adjustment, if any. The argument, if supplied, should
		simply be the number of hours difference between your local
		time and the talker's time.
		This difference can be specified to the nearest half hour.
EXAMPLE		tzadjust -6.5
		tzadjust +9
